  "body": "Use the docker image on Google GCP with Container Optimised OS (1 CPU - 4GB RAM- SSD)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nWhen I start the container the Node is syncing for a while.\r\nThen I get this Error:\r\n\r\nWARN [07-20|10:54:28.439] Checkpoint challenge timed out, dropping id=***** conn=dyndial addr=********:30303   type=Geth/v1.9.9-stable-01744997/linux-amd64/go1.13.5\r\nINFO [07-20|10:54:28.457] Imported new state entries               count=814  elapsed=8.124ms     processed=80394540 pending=35995 retry=261  duplicate=2171 unexpected=11440\r\nWARN [07-20|10:54:34.114] Checkpoint challenge timed out, dropping id=d775bde9d1b9d86e conn=dyndial addr=**********:30303    type=Geth/v1.9.16-stable-ea3b00ad/linux-amd64/go1.14.4\r\nERROR[07-20|10:54:53.985] Failed to unregister sync peer           peer=****** err=\"peer is not registered\"\r\n\r\nAnd the node stop syncing, but the process does not crash.\r\n\r\nWhen I restart the container the syncing starts again for a while until it fails again \r\n\r\nhere is the container creation command:\r\n\r\ndocker run -d --name ethereum-node -h 0.0.0.0 --restart always -v /mnt/stateful_partition/var/ethereum:/root \\\r\n           -p 8545:8545 -p 8546:8546 -p 30303:30303 \\\r\n           ethereum/client-go --ws --ws.addr \"0.0.0.0\" --http --http.addr \"0.0.0.0\"\r\n",
